6:
Hmm... I don't know, what do you
think?
13:
Well, in that case... Do you think it
might be okay to try... this?
22:
What are you two doing, all holed up
in here?
31:
Alk, great timing. Could you look at
this—
36:
W-wait a second! No way! I can't
show anyone my drawings, they're
nothing but scribbles!
39:
I, uh... I'm in the process of coming
up with a new outfit for Halloween.
Well, it's more like an entirely new
body frame, but you get what I
mean.
43: That sounds like a fun idea!
48:
It is. The new outfit is very cute. You
should take a look at—
53:
We don't need any more feedback!
The design is more or less decided
on, so...
57:
Okay, no problem. I'll just have to
look forward to seeing the final
product for myself!
59:
You mentioned a new body frame
though... Does that mean you're
swapping out your entire body? How
will you do that?
63:
That part will be handled by YOURS
TRULY, of course!
67:
We'll be using a specialized parts
shop. Actually, technology's
developed enough to the point that
they can now replace your entire
body!
72:
Oh come now. We've gone so long
without seeing each other—you
could at least acknowledge my
timely entrance!
76:
Oh, Regis. I didn't see you there. This
isn't a work-related matter, so... you
can feel free to leave.
80:
The World Flipper is just through the
door and up the stairs here. 
It should be very easy to find.
86:
You know, if I had feelings, they'd be
really hurt right about now.
87:
Anyway. To more practical matters;
do you have any idea what a
full-body outfitting costs? How do
you intend to pay for that?
90:
I figured we could just find cheaper
alternatives for the individual parts.
We don't need to buy the most
expensive stuff or anything.
94:
No, no, no! How could I stand here
and allow our own diva to be
outfitted with such second-rate
parts? Surely you wouldn't be
satisfied with that either.
99:
*Sigh* This always happens when
you show up, Regis.
102:
All right, I get it. You want me to treat
this as if it's part of my job, right?
105:
If that's the case, I'll go all out. I won't
compromise on the quality!
108:
Haha, but of course. I wouldn't have
it any other way. I'll make sure it's to
your liking.
110:
Now if you wouldn't mind telling me
exactly what outfit you had in mind...
114:
Fine. But you CAN'T laugh when you
see it, okay?!
119: All eyes and electrons on me!
123:
Ta-da! Diva Media, ready to
perform!
134: Stella's at a complete loss for words!
138:
That is an incredible outfit! So this is
what you meant by a full body
replacement...
142: All eyes and electrons on me too!
151: N-now there are TWO of them!
161: There are two Divas... Am I dreaming?
165:
Haha, you are NOT! Pretty cool, huh?
I'm actually just controlling this
other one remotely.
167:
It's just a secondary unit. It can
replicate simple, familiar
movements. It even has a speaker
installed!
171:
Wow, the resemblance is eerie.
Technology is amazing, huh.
174:
So... this second one isn't really
you?
Hmm, yeah, it doesn't seem to be
responding at all.
179:
Um, Alk... Could you stop staring at
it—er, me—like that? It's
embarrassing...
183:
Ah, sorry! I didn't realize I was
staring... My bad...
188:
Performing a full body part
exchange like that was no easy task,
you know. It's not exactly a common
procedure.
190:
And most certainly not a CHEAP one,
either.
195:
Oh, you know you'll just end up
marking it off as a business expense
anyway. Besides, I want to test out
this new body of mine!
199:
It just so happens to come with
some brand-new functions!
208:
A brand-new energy-conversion
mechanism, just like the one
organics have! Oh, and a gustatory
cortex as well.
211:
That just means that I can eat AND
taste food now!
214:
No way, that's great! You always
wanted to be able to eat food!
219:
Let's try lots of different food
together.
227:
Oh! I just remembered what I want
to eat... Plain curry!
231: Plain? With... nothing in it? Why?
234: What do you mean? Simple is best!
238:
All right, let's do this! Diva Media,
special Halloween Edition, all
systems a go-GO!
